HEADWORD: Tolstoian
<hw>Tol*stoi"an</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to <etsep>Tolstoy</etsep>
(1828-1910).</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A follower of Tolstoy,
who advocates and practices manual labor, simplicity of living,
nonresistance, etc., holds that possession of wealth and ownership of
property are sinful, and in religion rejects all teachings not coming
from Christ himself.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

